.TH GENERATE_TABLE 1 "March 2026" "AutoReadme" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
generate_table \- Generate a Markdown table of files with emojis and descriptions
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B generate_table
[\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B generate_table
scans the current directory and generates a Markdown table listing all files (excluding ignored ones). Each file is assigned an emoji based on its type/extension, and includes a description field.
.PP
The output is designed to be piped into
.BR merge_table (1)
to combine with existing README.md entries.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-verbose
Enable verbose output showing MIME type detection and emoji selection process.
.SH OUTPUT FORMAT
The output is a Markdown table with the following columns:
.TP
.B File
The filename
.TP
.B 🧿
An emoji representing the file type
.TP
.B Description
A brief description (initially empty, filled by merge_table)
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Generate table for current directory:
.B generate_table
.TP
Generate table with verbose output:
.B generate_table \-v
.TP
Pipe to merge with README:
.B generate_table | merge_table README.md
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ignore_list.txt
Local ignore list file
.TP
.B ~/.config/autoreadme/ignore_list.txt
User-specific ignore list (takes precedence)
.TP
.B .gitignore
Git ignore rules are respected
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR merge_table (1),
.BR autoreadme (1),
.BR checkreadme (1)
.SH AUTHOR
AutoReadme project